Because it allows the RFB to be the first truly ambidextrous 7.62 NATO Bullpup ever developed.No Trade, The patented, dual-extractor system maintains control of the case from the moment it leaves the magazine and upon firing, pulls the fired case from the chamber and lifts them to push them into an ejection chute above the barrel, where they exit. Furthermore, the stock and mechanism cross-section is similar to a conventional rifle, in stark contrast to existing Bullpup rifles.

title: For Sale:  Brand New in Box Del-Ton Sport!
postcontent:
This rifle is BNIB and comes with one brand new D&H 30 round magazine and a brand new rear iron sight so it is ready for you to shoot (extra $90 value)

You can read a review of this model here: GunBlast.com Review

The DT Sport proved to be one hundred percent reliable, as expected. The carbine fed, fired, and ejected every cartridge perfectly. Accuracy was excellent, especially considering the mil-spec trigger. I do much better work with a match trigger, such as the Alexander or Timney, but this carbine is built for fighting, and the trigger is well-suited to that task. The AR-15 is a wonderful concept, and Del-Ton executes it very well. The Del-Ton rifles are built very well, and just because the DT Sport is one of the most affordable AR-15 carbines available, does not mean that it sacrifices on quality. The DT Sport has everything that you need, and nothing that you don’t. It performs as well as rifles costing three times the price, and buying a basic rifle such as this leaves a lot more cash to purchase a good optic, plenty of extra magazines, and ammunition. You can’t have too much ammunition. The stuff keeps well, needs no refrigeration, and several thousand rounds will fit neatly under your bed. Buy it while you still can.

Also spec info easily found here:

http://www.del-ton.com/DT_Sport_p/dtsport.htm

Thanks for looking!

title: For Trade:  Grade A Hk P7
postcontent: This one is about to head back to the safe.  If my P7 m13 trades I will be keeping this.  I would prefer to trade or part trade for a P210, but will listen to offers.  I would consider a multi gun trade, but don't offer Taurus or other garbage.  Maybe a newer Desert Eagle .44 that functions perfectly.  I have an Hk P7 PSP to partial trade for a Sig P210 legend.  A target model would be the top of the list.  I've owned the P7 for about 8 years, it's in great shape and never failed me in any way.  It is one of the finest combat handguns ever made with a superb single action trigger.  The magazine release is a heel release.  I actually prefer this for CCW since there is no concern of the mag release button being hit and releasing the mag.  Comes with 2 mags and custom leather holster.  The P7 is one of the fastest weapons to reload due to the fact that the grip safety also releases the slide and cocks the weapon making it ready to fire.  The fixed polygonal rifled barrel lends to it's accuracy.  Some say the most accurate 9mm made.  The gas system allows for less recoil as well as assisting with the ejecting of brass due to ports in the chamber area.  The gas system also retards recoil for a fraction of a second so that the movement of recoil does not start until after the round has left the barrel.  The weapon will eject brass even if the extractor is damaged.  The gas system also prevents limp wrist issues.  One of the finest weapons ever!  I will always keep one in the collection (also have a P7m13).  I will consider a decent cash offer but don't waste my time with lowball offers please.   These are currently going for $1,200-$1,500.  The weapons is in my name so the purchaser must be legal to own and willing to complete a transfer form.  $1,200 or best offer.  Thanks
